        "## Workflow 5: Full Isolated Sampling\n\n### What Changed\n\n**KSampler_ZIMG** is now fully connected. The entire sampling pipeline runs in the isolated child process:\n\n- ModelSamplingAuraFlow_ZIMG → KSampler_ZIMG\n- CLIPTextEncode_ZIMG → KSampler_ZIMG (positive)\n- ConditioningZeroOut_ZIMG → KSampler_ZIMG (negative)\n- EmptySD3LatentImage_ZIMG → KSampler_ZIMG (latent)\n\nBut the loaders (UNET, CLIP, VAE) are still **host-side** feeding into isolated nodes via proxies.\n\n### What Crosses the Process Boundary\n\nAll proxy types are now active simultaneously:\n\n- **MODEL** (ModelPatcher proxy)\n- **CLIP** (CLIPProxy)\n- **CONDITIONING** (zero-copy tensors)\n- **LATENT** (zero-copy tensors)\n- **VAE** (VAEProxy) for final decode\n\n### The Sampling Loop\n\nThe KSampler runs `comfy.sample.sample()` in the child. During each denoising step, the child’s ModelPatcherProxy calls back to the host to execute `apply_model()` on the real GPU model. Tensors transfer via CUDA IPC — zero copy.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
